 of an insurance company to pay punctually senior policyholder claims and obligations and also reflect the expected financial loss suffered in the event of default specific obligations are considered unrated unless they are individually rated because the standing of a particular insurance obligation would depend on an assessment of its relative standing under those laws governing both the obligation and the insurance company ratings explanations can be found at wwwmoodyscom sp global insurer financial strength rating is a forwardlooking opinion about the financial security characteristics of an insurance organization with respect to its ability to pay under its insurance policies and contracts in accordance with their terms this opinion is not specific to any particular policy or contract nor does it address the suitability of a particular policy or contract for a specific purpose or purchaser ratings explanations can be found at wwwstandardandpoorscom   the center for annuity awareness  copyright   all rights reserved first name  last name  age  zip code  email  phone number  currently retired  yes no investment amount         dont know get your rates how much could an annuity pay you  our free annuities guide guaranteed retirement income learn what your rates and monthly income could be in retirement rates can vary by clicking the submit button you give us expressed written consent to call or text you at the phone number provided even if it is a mobile phone number to discuss your annuity options by clicking the button you also agree that we may use a computer or other automatic dialing technology to call you or text you even if computerized dialing is used there will be a human not a recorded message on the call when you pick up clicking submit is not a condition of purchase fixed income annuity with rider plus our free download to learn who benefits from an annuity how they can address your financial concerns simple explanation of fixed annuities variable annuit